main event: A bright, round light was observed by a lieutenant near Tyndall Air Force Base, Florida on January 8, 1955.
interesting points: The object was described as a 'round, very bright light'.
The report concluded the object was 'Probable meteor'.
The sighting was also reported by local civilians and an air evacuation unit in the area.
Eglin Air Force Base reported no range activity at the time of the sighting.
location: 20 miles north of Tyndall AFB, Florida
